messages.message:
How do folks feel about putting README.md documents in our code source tree to give overviews of useful packages?

E.g., I’m about to merge in a `data-export-utils` package that, I think, can become a global place for us to define iterators that take {file_set} -> {file_set}… with automated type+constraint-checking of file sets, file marshaling, reads/writes, etc. (it’s neat!)

… but for it to be practically used it probably wants a high level overview of the sort that doesn’t really fit in as pydocs in any particular file..
